TITLE: Biden brings more troops and sanctions to NATO amid rising fears of Russian chemical warfare
SUMMARY: Preparing for the next phase of Putin's war against Ukraine is the centerpiece of Biden's NATO meeting this week, amid rising fears of Russian chemical weapons.

TITLE: Supreme Court nominee Ketanji Brown Jackson wraps tense two days of Senate questioning as confirmation path clears
SUMMARY: Jackson, President Biden's first Supreme Court nominee, already spent more than 13 hours before the Senate Judiciary Committee defending her judicial career.

TITLE: U.S. government formally accuses Russia of committing war crimes in Ukraine
SUMMARY: Secretary of State Antony Blinken formally announced Wednesday that the United States government believes Russia has committed war crimes in Ukraine.

TITLE: NATO leaders set to OK 'major increases' of troops in response to Putin's war on Ukraine
SUMMARY: Ukraine, which has sought NATO membership since 2002, is bordered by four NATO allies.

TITLE: Up to 40,000 Russian soldiers killed, wounded, captured or MIA in Ukraine, NATO estimates
SUMMARY: The Pentagon has previously denied confirming any reported estimates on the number of Russian troops that have been removed from battle.

TITLE: Trump withdraws endorsement of Alabama Senate candidate Mo Brooks, who urged GOP to stop questioning 2020 election
SUMMARY: Rep. Mo Brooks of Alabama lost Donald Trump's backing for his Senate race despite endorsing claims that President Joe Biden won the 2020 election by fraud.

TITLE: One of Putin’s top aides quits, reportedly in opposition to the Ukraine war
SUMMARY: A high-ranking and long-standing aide to Russian President Vladimir Putin has quit his role due to his opposition to Russia's invasion of Ukraine

TITLE: White House press secretary Jen Psaki has Covid, will miss Biden trip to Europe
SUMMARY: This is the second time that White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki tested positive for coronavirus and will miss traveling with President Joe Biden.

TITLE: Henry Cuellar becomes latest Democrat to distance himself from Koch Industries over company's Russia ties
SUMMARY: Henry Cuellar is the latest Democratic lawmaker to distance from Koch as the company continues its business in Russia.

TITLE: Supreme Court pick Ketanji Brown Jackson grilled on sentencing record, social issues in Senate hearing
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden's Supreme Court nominee, Ketanji Brown Jackson, answered senators' questions during her confirmation hearings.

TITLE: Porn star Stormy Daniels loses appeal in Trump case, vows 'I will go to jail before I pay a penny' of $300,000
SUMMARY: The court ruling likely ends a long legal feud between former President Donald Trump and porn star Stormy Daniels, who says they once had sex.

TITLE: Koch Industries' campaign donations questioned after company's decision to remain in Russia
SUMMARY: Lawmakers are facing scrutiny for seeing support from Koch Industries as the company remains in Russia following the invasion of Ukraine.

TITLE: Washington’s ‘trigger-happy’ sanctions may push countries away from the dollar, says think tank
SUMMARY: Central banks are starting to question whether reliance on the U.S. dollar is a good idea, said Gal Luft of the Institute for the Analysis of Global Security.

TITLE: SEC proposes broad climate rules as Chair Gensler says risk disclosure will help investors
SUMMARY: The SEC proposed rules that would require companies to report on how their operations affect the climate and the formation of carbon emissions.

TITLE: Russia says Biden's 'war criminal' claim has put relations 'on the verge of rupture'
SUMMARY: Russia says President Joe Biden's decision to label Vladimir Putin a "war criminal"  has put "Russian-American relations on the verge of rupture."

TITLE: Supreme Court pick Ketanji Brown Jackson defends record in Senate confirmation hearing
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden's first Supreme Court nominee, Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson, appeared for the first of four days of Senate hearings.

TITLE: Putin's Russia looks increasingly desperate as Ukraine war nears stalemate, analysts say
SUMMARY: Putin's forces have exerted brutal force and destruction on much of Ukraine, but Russia has achieved few military victories.

TITLE: Oligarch Roman Abramovich's $50 million Colorado mansion could become a sanctions target
SUMMARY: A Rocky Mountain mansion owned by Russian oligarch Roman Abramovich would likely be among the first assets frozen by the U.S. government if he is sanctioned.

TITLE: Xi 'can't stomach doing something that might make Putin look bad,' says political analyst
SUMMARY: China doesn't want to take a position on Ukraine that could undermine Russia, said Scott Kennedy of the Center for Strategic and International Studies.

TITLE: U.S. officials continue to press Russia for access to WNBA star Brittney Griner
SUMMARY: A person close to the situation confirmed to NBC News that Griner was "OK" and that her Russian legal team has met with her.

TITLE: Biden warns Xi of global backlash if China helps Russia's attack on Ukraine
SUMMARY: Biden and Chinese Pres. Xi Jinping agreed to work for peace in Ukraine. But China refused to say Russia was responsible for its brutal invasion of the country.

TITLE: Here's what Chinese state media is saying ahead of Xi's call with Biden
SUMMARY: While Chinese state media have tacked away from primarily pro-Russian coverage of the war with Ukraine, one of the consistent messages remains: Blame the U.S.

TITLE: How the Russia-Ukraine war could hit China's trade
SUMMARY: China's trade surplus could narrow to $238 billion this year – about 35% of the historic $676 billion attained last year, according to ANZ Research estimates.

TITLE: Ex-New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo considers running against Kathy Hochul despite opposition from his own party
SUMMARY: Andrew Cuomo is speaking with allies about possibly running against New York Gov. Kathy Hochul. Democratic Party officials scoff at the idea.

TITLE: Russia makes some debt payments in dollars, report says, as it seeks to avoid historic debt default
SUMMARY: The payment on the two eurobond coupons is a key test for Russia.

TITLE: Biden details new aid to Ukraine, promises "more in the days and weeks ahead" to help combat Russia invasion
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden condemned Russian leader Vladimir Putin for inflicting "appalling devastation" on Ukraine.

TITLE: Ukraine President Zelenskyy invokes Pearl Harbor, Sept. 11 in asking U.S. Congress to help fight Russia invasion
SUMMARY: Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenskyy addressed Congress seeking more aid to fight against its invasion by Russia.

TITLE: White House says U.S. will run out of money to fight pandemic if Congress doesn't pass Covid funding bill
SUMMARY: The White House is urging Congress to pass $22.5 billion in Covid spending, warning the U.S. is running out of money to fight the virus.

TITLE: Biden signs government funding bill that includes $13.6 billion in Ukraine aid
SUMMARY: Biden signed a funding bill that will keep the government running through September and send $13.6 billion in aid to Ukraine.

TITLE: U.S. lobbyists connect Ukraine officials with powerful allies to help in war against Russia
SUMMARY: At least one U.S. company and a separate lawyer each recently disclosed to DOJ that they started working for Ukrainian officials since the Russian invasion.
